<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Task//EN" "task.dtd" []>
<task xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" id="splitting-element" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:oasis:names:tc:dita:xsd:task.xsd:1.1">
  <title>Splitting Element</title>
  <taskbody id="body">
    <context>
      <p>You can split an element one of these ways:</p>
    </context>
    <steps-unordered>
      <step>
        <cmd>Split an element in the Editing Window.</cmd>
        <substeps>
          <substep>
            <cmd>Place the cursor in the element in the Editing Window.</cmd>
          </substep>
          <substep>
            <cmd>Split the element.</cmd>
            <info>
              <p>Do one of the following:<ul>
                  <li>
                    <p>Press <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p>Choose <menucascade>
                        <uicontrol>Element</uicontrol>
                        <uicontrol>Split Element</uicontrol>
                      </menucascade>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p>Click the <uicontrol>Split Element</uicontrol> button <image href="split-element-button.png" align="center" placement="inline"/> on the toolbar.</p>
                  </li>
                </ul></p>
            </info>
          </substep>
        </substeps>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Split the parent of an element in the Editing Window.</cmd>
        <substeps>
          <substep>
            <cmd>Place the cursor in the element in the Editing Window.</cmd>
          </substep>
          <substep>
            <cmd>Press <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol> twice.</cmd>
            <info>
              <p>This is called <i>advanced</i> element split.</p>
            </info>
          </substep>
        </substeps>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Split the parent of the parent (and so on) of an element in the Editing Window.</cmd>
        <substeps>
          <substep>
            <cmd>Place the cursor in the element in the Editing Window.</cmd>
          </substep>
          <substep>
            <cmd>Press <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol> multiple times in a row.</cmd>
            <info>
              <p>This is called <i>advanced</i> element split.</p>
            </info>
          </substep>
        </substeps>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Split an element in ContentMap.</cmd>
        <substeps>
          <substep>
            <cmd>Click the element in ContentMap.</cmd>
          </substep>
          <substep>
            <cmd>Split the element.</cmd>
            <info>
              <p>Do one of the following:<ul>
                  <li>
                    <p>Choose <menucascade>
                        <uicontrol>Element</uicontrol>
                        <uicontrol>Split Element</uicontrol>
                      </menucascade>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p>Click the <uicontrol>Split Element</uicontrol> button <image href="split-element-button.png" align="center" placement="inline"/> on the toolbar.</p>
                  </li>
                </ul></p>
            </info>
          </substep>
        </substeps>
        <info>
          <note>
            <p>The <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol> key won&apos;t work to split elements in ContentMap and consequently the <i>advanced split</i> won&apos;t work.</p>
          </note>
        </info>
      </step>
    </steps-unordered>
    <example>
      <title>Example. Splitting elements.</title>
      <p>Suppose we have inserted <codeph>itemizedlist</codeph>-&gt;<codeph>listitem</codeph>-&gt;<codeph>para</codeph>.</p>
      <fig frame="all">
        <image href="inserted-listitem.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
      </fig>
      <ol>
        <li>
          <p>Type &quot;<codeph>OrangeLemon</codeph>&quot; in the <codeph>para</codeph>. Place the cursor between the words.</p>
          <fig frame="all">
            <image href="cursor-between-words-in-para.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
          </fig>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Press <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol>.</p>
          <p>The <codeph>para</codeph> will be split (a new <codeph>para</codeph> will be inserted).</p>
          <fig frame="all">
            <image href="split-para.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
          </fig>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Press <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol> immediately again.</p>
          <p>This will split the first  <codeph>listitem</codeph>.</p>
          <fig frame="all">
            <image href="split-advanced.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
          </fig>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </example>
  </taskbody>
</task>
